<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons" rel="stylesheet">
    <link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="css/materialize.min.css"  media="screen,projection"/>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
    <%- include('meta'); -%>
    <title>API Docs - <%= name %></title>
    <Style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            min-height: 100vh;
            flex-direction: column;
        }
        .container {
            flex: 1 0 auto;
        }
        .container {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            position: relative;
        }
        #nobg {
            -webkit-box-shadow: none  !important;
            -moz-box-shadow: none  !important;
            box-shadow: none  !important;
            background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0) !important;
        }
    </Style>
</head>
<!--<body style="background: url('assets/bg.jpg'); background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: cover;"> -->
<body style="background-color: #232323;">
<%- include('header'); -%>
<div class="container">
    <div class="row center white-text" style="width: 100%;">
        <div class="col s12">
            <h3><%= name %> API</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="col s12">
            <h4>GET requests</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="rows">
            <div class="col s4">
                <h5>Generating shortened URL</h5>
                <p>Make a GET request to <code><%= url %>/api/generate?url=URL HERE</code></p>
                <p>For example: <code><%= url %>/api/generate?url=example.com</code></p>
                <p>It will return the shortened URL. Example: <code><%= url %>/abcdef</code></p>
            </div>
            <div class="col s4">
                <h5>Resolving a code</h5>
                <p>Make a get request to <code><%= url %>/api/resolve?code=CODE HERE</code></p>
                <p>For example: <code><%= url %>/api/resolve?code=abcdef</code></p>
                <p>It will return the resolved URL. Example: <code>http://example.com/abcdef</code></p>
            </div>
            <div class="col s4">
                <h5>Getting clicks</h5>
                <p>Make a get request to <code><%= url %>/api/clicks?code=CODE HERE</code></p>
                <p>For example: <code><%= url %>/api/clicks?code=abcdef</code></p>
                <p>It will return all clicks as a number.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="divider"></div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col s12">
                <h4>JSON</h4>
                <p>You can fetch codes data in JSON:<br>Make a get request to <code><%= url %>/json/CODE HERE</code></p>
                <p><code><%= url %>/json/abcdef</code> should get you: <br></p>
                <pre class="left-align"><code>
                        {
                            "code": "abcdef",
                            "url": "http://example.com",
                            "clicks": 30
                        }
                    </code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<%- include('footer'); -%>
<script type="text/javascript" src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.2.1.min.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript" src="js/materialize.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
